datos_anuales <- base %>%
  count(QPC_Criteria_Order, Status) %>% 
  mutate(
    QPC_Criteria_Order = factor(QPC_Criteria_Order),
    Status = factor(Status)
  )

# Crear etiquetas en la posición correcta (acumuladas)
etiquetas <- datos_anuales %>%
  group_by(QPC_Criteria_Order) %>%
  arrange(QPC_Criteria_Order, desc(Status)) %>%
  mutate(
    posicion_cumulativa = cumsum(n),
    posicion_etiqueta = posicion_cumulativa - (n / 2)
  )

# Obtener número único de estados para la paleta de colores
num_estados <- nlevels(datos_anuales$Status)

# Obtener las etiquetas actuales del factor
etiquetas_actuales <- levels(datos_anuales$QPC_Criteria_Order)

# Reemplazar las primeras dos etiquetas
etiquetas_nuevas <- etiquetas_actuales
etiquetas_nuevas[1] <- "External"
etiquetas_nuevas[2] <- "Fiscal"

ggplot(datos_anuales, aes(x = QPC_Criteria_Order, y = n, fill = Status)) +
  geom_col(position = position_stack(), color = "black", width = 0.7) +
  geom_text(
    data = etiquetas,
    aes(y = posicion_etiqueta, label = ifelse(n > 0, n, "")),
    size = 3,
    family = "sans",
    color = "white",
    fontface = "bold"
  ) +
  scale_fill_manual(
    values = colorRampPalette(c("#3A5F7F", "#A83232"))(num_estados)
  ) +
  scale_x_discrete(labels = etiquetas_nuevas) +
  labs(x = "", y = "QPCs", fill = "Status") +
  theme_minimal(base_family = "sans", base_size = 11) +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(  # Eliminamos la rotación de 90°

p <- ncol(training_set)

p
## [1] 905
round(sqrt(p))
## [1] 30

## [1] 90

## [1] 814
grid <- expand.grid(
  ntree = c(500, 1000),
  mtry = unique(pmax(1, c(round(sqrt(p)), round(p*0.1), round(p*0.3)))),
  nodesize = c(1, 2),
  maxnodes = c(NA, 20)  # NA = sin límite
)
# levels(training_set$Status)
# 
# class_w <- c("0" = 0.5, "1" = 0.5)
# 
# freq <- table(training_set$Status)
# freq
# sum(freq)
# length(freq)
# round(prop.table(summary(training_set$Status)),3)
# 
# class_w <- as.numeric((freq)/sum(freq))
# class_w
# 
# class_w_normalized <- class_w / sum(class_w)
# class_w_normalized
# 
# names(class_w_normalized) <- names(freq)

class_w_normalized <- NULL
best_metric <- -Inf
best_params <- NULL
for (i in seq_len(nrow(grid))) {
  params <- grid[i, ]
  
  # Separate predictors and response
  x_train <- training_set[, !names(training_set) %in% "Status"]
  y_train <- training_set$Status
  
  # Build the model with or without classwt
  if(!is.null(class_w_normalized)) {
    rf <- randomForest(
      x = x_train,        # Only predictor variables
      y = y_train,        # Response variable
      ntree = params$ntree,
      mtry = params$mtry,
      nodesize = params$nodesize,
      maxnodes = if (is.na(params$maxnodes)) NULL else params$maxnodes,
      classwt = class_w_normalized,
      keep.forest = TRUE,
      do.trace = FALSE
    )
  } else {
    rf <- randomForest(
      x = x_train,
      y = y_train,
      ntree = params$ntree,
      mtry = params$mtry,
      nodesize = params$nodesize,
      maxnodes = if (is.na(params$maxnodes)) NULL else params$maxnodes,
      keep.forest = TRUE,
      do.trace = FALSE
    )
  }
  
  # Prediction on VALIDATION
  # For validation, also remove the Status column
  validation_predictors <- validation_set[, !names(validation_set) %in% "Status"]
  prob_val <- predict(rf, newdata = validation_predictors, type = "prob")[, 2]
  
  auc_val <- as.numeric(auc(response = validation_set$Status, predictor = prob_val))
  
  if (is.finite(auc_val) && auc_val > best_metric) {
    best_metric <- auc_val
    best_params <- params
  }
}

accuracy <- (TP + TN) / sum(confmatrix)

## Accuracy: 0.8888889

cat("Precision:", precision, "\n")
## Precision: 0.5555556
recall <- TP / (TP + FN)
cat("Recall:", recall, "\n")
## Recall: 0.625
f1_score <- 2 * (precision * recall) / (precision + recall)
cat("F1 Score:", f1_score, "\n")

library(dplyr)

sum_access <- sum(test$Totalaccess)

test <- test %>%
  mutate(w = Totalaccess / sum_access)

test$PredictedStatus <- predicted_total_enteros

test <- test %>%
  mutate(
    TP = ifelse(Status == 1 & PredictedStatus == 1, 1, 0),
    FP = ifelse(Status == 0 & PredictedStatus == 1, 1, 0),
    FN = ifelse(Status == 1 & PredictedStatus == 0, 1, 0)
  )

weighted_TP <- sum(test$w * test$TP)
weighted_FP <- sum(test$w * test$FP)
weighted_FN <- sum(test$w * test$FN)

weighted_F1 <- (2 * weighted_TP) / (2 * weighted_TP + weighted_FP + weighted_FN)

cat(sprintf("Weighted F1 Score: %.7f\n", weighted_F1))
## Weighted F1 Score: 0.8914687

cat("Accuracy:", accuracy, "\n")
## Accuracy: 0.952381
precision <- TP / (TP + FP)
cat("Precision:", precision, "\n")
## Precision: 1
recall <- TP / (TP + FN)
cat("Recall:", recall, "\n")
## Recall: 0.625
f1_score <- 2 * (precision * recall) / (precision + recall)
cat("F1 Score:", f1_score, "\n")
## F1 Score: 0.7692308

predictions_test <- predict(model2, newdata = test, type = "prob")

roc_NETtrain <- roc(validation_set$Status, predictions_train[, 2])
roc_NET <- roc(test$Status, predictions_test[, 2])

common_points <- seq(0, 1, length.out = 100)
roc_NET_interp_train <- approx(roc_NETtrain$specificities, roc_NETtrain$sensitivities, xout = common_points)
roc_NET_interp <- approx(roc_NET$specificities, roc_NET$sensitivities, xout = common_points)
roc_data <- data.frame(
  FPR = c(roc_NET_interp_train$x, roc_NET_interp$x),
  TPR = c(roc_NET_interp_train$y, roc_NET_interp$y),
  Model = factor(rep(c("RF (train)", "RF (test)"), each = length(common_points)))
)

library(ggplot2)
